23 Sep 2016 22:21






I don't really have a particular problem, with the writing itself, but the science here actually isn't entirely correct! It's obviously not the most important thing, but the justifications used don't actually make sense with how the human body works.

First, females are born with all the ova they will have for their whole life. They aren't produced one at a time they're already all there. They get released from the ovary one at a time (usually) and are shedded if they aren't impregnated. But they are already all there, much like sperm in a male's testicles. Fertlization in this manner would only be safe and effective for women nearing menopause.

Secondly. Two ova from one mother fused together would not make a genetically identical child. Durig the process of meiosis, the chromosomes actually 'cross over', swapping some of their genetic information. So each ovum actually is genetically different. It's why siblings can look so radically different!

Thirdly, though this is more minor. Oocytes are very large. I imagine this can just be ignored easily enough

Anyway, I'm not trying to say the SCP is bad! It's an interesting concept. But it may be better to say it spontaneously impregnates you with a clone than the current explanation, because in terms of actual genetics and reproductive science, it doesn't really work.

Either that, or you alter it so that traditionally only menopausal women do this in the village to reproduce, and have little girls dumped in the springs also explode with fetuses. Things to consider!







